# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env.local` for: vercel dev   (loads these for /api/* routes)
# Production: Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables → same names
# Never commit `.env` / `.env.local` with real secrets.
# =============================================================================

# ----- Gemini (REQUIRED for Agent + AI chat) — server-side only -----
# https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Optional (default in api/agent.js: gemini-1.5-flash)
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-1.5-flash

# Same as GEMINI_API_KEY if you prefer the name (api/agent.js accepts either)
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# ----- Anam AI avatar -----
# Persona UUID from https://lab.anam.ai (Widget tab embed). No spaces or quotes.
ANAM_PERSONA_ID=fa39aabd-ad5c-438f-b094-62bb8d818674

# Optional — server-only. GET /api/anam-session mints a session-token for the widget.
# If unset, the site uses agent-id + Lab domain allowlist only.
ANAM_API_KEY=7566ff74-8fcb-48bb-9cb8-8bddcf5ec570

# =============================================================================
# Anam: "This agent is not authorized. Check your agent ID" (403 / 401)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Anam Lab → your persona → Widget → Allowed domains:
#    add EXACTLY your site origin, e.g. https://your-project.vercel.app
#    (include https, no trailing slash). Add www and non-www if you use both.
# 2) Same tab: enable "Allow everywhere" temporarily to confirm it is a domain issue.
# 3) Click Publish on the persona after changes.
# 4) Vercel → Environment Variables: set ANAM_PERSONA_ID (and optional ANAM_API_KEY).
#    Under "Environments", enable Production AND Preview (GitHub deploys often use Preview).
# 5) Redeploy after changing env vars (Deployments → ... → Redeploy).
# 6) Persona ID must match Lab (UUID). No extra quotes/spaces in Vercel.
# =============================================================================

# Not read by serverless routes — still edit in the repo:
#   OpenWeather  → script.js CONFIG.weatherAPIKey
#   Google Maps  → index.html maps script URL
#   Firebase     → script.js firebaseConfig
